            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I think the current behavior is useful and should not be changed.\n\n`getchar()` is there to get a character from the user. I don't see why whether that character is mapped to something should matter for the `getchar()` behavior.\n\nIt is not *particularly* problematic for plugins (needs an extra check for `\\3`), but having no way to cancel the input due to the sheer presence of a mapping (even a useless one like `nnoremap <C-c> <C-c>`) is not consistent.",
